description.narrative: (Tanzania): With FY 2020 funds, the Boresha Afya North/Central activity will support preventive and curative services for family planning (FP), HIV/AIDS, and tuberculosis (TB) in five regions: Arusha, Kilimanjaro, Manyara, Dodoma, and Singida. In Tabora, EGPAF will support HIV, FP and TB. Tailored approaches have been rolled out in designated scale-up and sustained districts, and differentiated models of care are employed to improve the quality of services and responsiveness to individual client needs in general. The activity will strengthen the continuum of care through strategic integration of FP, HIV, and TB services within facilities, communities, districts, regions, and the broader health system. The activity is working side-by-side with District Councils as a strategic partner, providing subgrants coupled with technical assistance. The activity will also continue to coordinate with other implementing partners in the supported regions to create synergies and to avoid duplication of effort.....
